		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_BUILDING_MAGISTRATE_OFFICE_DESC">
			<Text>The needs of an expanding empire require an army of local officials to maintain law and order. As states evolved different configurations of power emerged as well. For some states, the absolute power of the centre and the subjugation of the law to that centre required a similar fusion of power throughout the empire. In these cases the magistrates came to fulfill a unique role as they both possed judiciary and legislative powers within their own jurisdictions.</Text>
